    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order of flowering plants consisting of 2 families, 27 genera, and about 300 species. Members are herbs or shrubs, rarely hemiparasites, and largely restricted to tropical or temperate arid or saline regions. The flowers are showy and possess oil or nectar glands for bee pollination.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
